creator: Eulalie Osgood Grover
description:
LibriVox recording of Kittens and Cats: A Book of Tales by Eulalie Osgood Grover.

Read in English by Rosslyn Carlyle.

This book consists of fifty-two very short fictitious stories about cats and kittens, which have been written for children. Many of the stories have been written by cats and address the queen, many of them are commentaries on well known nursery rhymes, and many of them are both. - Summary by Rosslyn Carlyle

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (14MB)
